  "prompt": "Can you state the law of conservation of mass?",
  "response": "The law of conservation of mass states that in a closed system, the total mass of the substances remains constant during a chemical reaction or physical change. In other words, the total mass of the reactants before a chemical reaction is equal to the total mass of the products after the reaction. Matter cannot be created or destroyed, only transformed from one form to another.\n\nThis fundamental principle was first proposed by Antoine Lavoisier in the late 18th century and is a key concept in chemistry and physics.",
